comments: I noticed the shapes and colours had different prefixes and suffixes - wop for a circle, zet for a star, gaf for a cross and buv for a pentagon. I tried to pick these up first, then the colours. The pronunciations I found actually hindered me - I was trying to learn the words and their correct spelling. I found the first part easier, but the individual I was matched with I think had learned the phonetic spellings as opposed to the 'real' spellings making it hard and frustrating.
